  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Momo was a brown, medium-sized dog who normally spent her whole day sleeping quietly by the gate.",
      "zh": "Momo 是一隻棕色的中型狗，平常一整天都安靜地在校門口睡覺。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Every other animal near the school, from birds to the neighborhood cats, seemed to ignore the same smell completely.",
      "zh": "學校附近的其他動物，從鳥到附近的貓，似乎都完全沒注意到同樣的味道。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The guard's dog was named Momo, and everyone at school agreed she was the calmest dog they had ever met.",
      "zh": "警衛的狗叫 Momo，全校都同意牠是他們見過最溫和的狗。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Except, apparently, at exactly 3:33 every afternoon.",
      "zh": "除了每天下午三點三十三分那一刻，顯然不是這樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"She just starts barking,\" the guard said. \"At nothing. Same time, every single day.\"",
      "zh": "警衛說：「她就是開始叫，對著空氣叫，每天都一樣的時間。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice checked her watch. \"It's 3:20. Thirteen minutes until show time.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 看了看手錶：「現在三點二十分，還有十三分鐘就要開演了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "At 3:33 exactly, Momo stood up, faced the school gate, and barked five times, loudly.",
      "zh": "三點三十三分整，Momo 站起來，面向校門，大聲叫了五聲。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Then she sat back down, completely calm again, as if nothing had happened.",
      "zh": "接著她又坐回去，恢復完全平靜，好像什麼事都沒發生過一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"She's not scared,\" Coco said, watching closely. \"She looks... excited.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 仔細觀察後說：「她不是害怕，她看起來⋯⋯是興奮。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "They followed Momo's eyes and found she was always looking in the exact same direction: past the gate, toward the street.",
      "zh": "他們順著 Momo 的視線看過去，發現她每次都看著同一個方向：越過校門，朝著街道那邊。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"There's nothing unusual out there,\" Bernice said. \"Just the street. And that bakery on the corner.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 說：「外面沒什麼特別的，就是街道，還有轉角那間麵包店。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco went quiet for a second. \"Wait. What time does that bakery start baking bread?\"",
      "zh": "Coco 突然安靜了一下：「等等，那間麵包店幾點開始烤麵包？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Neither of them knew, but both of them suddenly had the exact same idea at the exact same moment.",
      "zh": "他們兩個都不知道，但兩個人在同一時間突然有了一模一樣的想法。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Tomorrow,\" Bernice said, \"we bring snacks. And we ask someone at the bakery some questions.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 說：「明天我們帶點零食去，順便問麵包店的人幾個問題。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan, hearing the plan, only had one comment. \"A case that ends at a bakery,\" he said. \"I like this one already.\"",
      "zh": "潘老師聽到這個計畫，只說了一句話：「一個結束在麵包店的案子，」他說：「我已經很喜歡這一個了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "That night, Coco added a new question to her notebook: was it possible for a mystery to solve itself, just by someone finally checking the time?",
      "zh": "那天晚上，Coco 在筆記本上加了一個新問題：一個謎團有沒有可能，只要有人終於去查一下時間，就自己解開了？"
    },
    {
      "en": "She wasn't sure yet, but she had a feeling this case would answer that question faster than any before it.",
      "zh": "她還不確定，但她有種感覺，這個案子解開的速度會比之前任何一個都快。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice, meanwhile, was already making a list of things to buy at the bakery, \"just to make sure they understood the case.\"",
      "zh": "與此同時，Bernice 已經在列一張要在麵包店買的東西清單，「只是為了把案子搞清楚。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That's not how investigating works,\" Coco said.",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「查案不是這樣查的。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"It is now,\" Bernice said, and closed her notebook with a happy smile.",
      "zh": "Bernice 說：「現在是了。」然後闔上筆記本，臉上帶著開心的笑容。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Dogs are smarter than people think,\" the guard said proudly. \"Momo even knows which days are holidays.\"",
      "zh": "警衛驕傲地說：「狗比大家想的還聰明，Momo 甚至知道哪天是假日。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I chose to become a school guard because I like quiet mornings,\" the guard admitted, scratching Momo behind the ear.",
      "zh": "警衛一邊搔著 Momo 的耳朵，一邊坦承：「我選擇當校警,是因為我喜歡安靜的早晨。」"
    }
  ],
